ivo when GATA3 is conditionally deleted in peripheral CD4 T cells.&nbsp; Th2 cells from both knockout animals showed reduction in IL-4 production. (Zhu J. 2004, Pai SY. 2004).  The GATA3 expression induced by TNF-&alpha; was enhanced in the presence of BPA.&nbsp; However, the T-bet expression did not change when tested at various culture conditions (Guo H. 2010, Uemura Y. 2008).&nbsp; IL-4 may serve multiple roles in the development of lupus: it may enhance autoantibody production via its direct B-cell effects (Ram RS. 2003).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:23:35 +0000 2026"}